notes:
Round One:
-

The items here are standard item picks for a weapon power based Cassidy build. [Compensator](item_2a354f80-610c-4661-9bdd-8960ae1a60b0) to increase weapon damage and [Plasma Converter](item_25869f9a-9a29-4e19-96b6-9d8a28c59318) to have some survivability

[Ammo Reserves](item_982d53aa-5ef4-493f-93e7-9e374d0ebf34) here is non-negotiable as ammo is a core part of the build

Round Two:
-

Minimally, the game will grace you with at least a 10k cash total but you should be able to net at least an 11k cash total.

This means that you should sell [Plasma Converter](item_25869f9a-9a29-4e19-96b6-9d8a28c59318) for [Technoleech](item_cb7fd8bf-bdcc-439a-ad35-372f24a027a8) 

However, you could also opt to sell both green items and get [Talon Modification Module](item_c0ca1795-a3ea-4dc9-ae17-f34122574b3a) instead to boost your killing power but lower survivability.

Cash Totals
-

[Technoleech](item_cb7fd8bf-bdcc-439a-ad35-372f24a027a8): 11k

[Talon Modification Module](item_c0ca1795-a3ea-4dc9-ae17-f34122574b3a): 11.5k

Round Three:
-

There are a few powers you should consider here. The first in line here would be [Just Roll With It](item_71918d53-d84e-48f1-9940-8fbe0d9d5a41) as it will cancel any burst damage that is going to be done or is in the process of being done towards you. This power is even more prominent now that Freja is in stadium as her Take Aim shot will generally remove you from existence immediately and this power greatly counters that.

The second power you can consider here is [Hot Potato](item_78b037fe-f73c-4fda-90b8-716da8e749bc) as it gives you more ammo for the fan which directly increases your damage against tanks or have more bullets to hit during a close up brawl with another dps/support.

As for items, you should sell [Stockpile](item_a113eb56-9999-4f22-9bd7-18f4dbd00cc2) or [Commander's Clip](item_ff7cad01-2065-4908-a2c1-3bdf1458c7a4) which puts you are a nice 10 ammo. Here, you may also choose to swap [Technoleech](item_cb7fd8bf-bdcc-439a-ad35-372f24a027a8) for [Talon Modification Module](item_c0ca1795-a3ea-4dc9-ae17-f34122574b3a) if you so choose to.

What we don't buy here is [Quickload Chamber](item_fc0bca6b-2c96-44bc-8d77-0acc8defa436) as in a duel with another dps or support, you either kill them during your initial burst or you are pretty much dead and you should not be near enough to any tanks for the item to work its magic as you should be fanning tanks at a decently safe distance which at times is more than 6 meters


Cash Totals
-

[Talon Modification Module](item_c0ca1795-a3ea-4dc9-ae17-f34122574b3a): 18.5k

Round Four:
-

There are a few routes you can pick to go on round four. The most generalist route is to pick up [Talon Modification Module](item_c0ca1795-a3ea-4dc9-ae17-f34122574b3a) as it is a sizable boost to your damage.

The second route you may choose to go is [Codebreaker](item_caa96c7e-655f-4d03-9bd9-0f41937fec27) against the armored tanks. This will allow you to burst away their HP with fan that much faster as ignoring 50% armor damage reduction is very impactful.

The third route that you can choose is [Frankie’s Fixer](item_6fb21e33-bbfa-4810-ba46-d9fbc6bbcc3a). This route will be the one you pick the most (as of current) as healing up from burst damage such as Freja's Take Aim shots without your healers will be paramount because they will generally be occupied with healing up the tanks. This significantly lowers the healing load for them as well as buffing up your survivability


Cash Totals
-

[Talon Modification Module](item_c0ca1795-a3ea-4dc9-ae17-f34122574b3a): 23k

[Frankie’s Fixer](item_6fb21e33-bbfa-4810-ba46-d9fbc6bbcc3a) + [Compensator](item_2a354f80-610c-4661-9bdd-8960ae1a60b0): 22.5k

[Frankie’s Fixer](item_6fb21e33-bbfa-4810-ba46-d9fbc6bbcc3a) + [Technoleech](item_cb7fd8bf-bdcc-439a-ad35-372f24a027a8): 26k

[Codebreaker](item_caa96c7e-655f-4d03-9bd9-0f41937fec27): 26k

Round Five:
-

Our power option here is only [Hot Potato](item_78b037fe-f73c-4fda-90b8-716da8e749bc) if you hadn't already picked it up on round 3. If you already have picked it up then it would be wise to pick up [Just Roll With It](item_71918d53-d84e-48f1-9940-8fbe0d9d5a41) to get out of burst damage situations which are now more prominent. But if you insist on wanting a more offensive power then [Flash in the Pan](item_b620b463-eda9-4cbe-9781-92fdaf862bdf)  or [Quick Draw](item_fce335e5-8093-4936-98c1-12ee26efd5d3) aren't bad ideas to have.

As for items, here you should force [Frankie’s Fixer](item_6fb21e33-bbfa-4810-ba46-d9fbc6bbcc3a) as damage has climbed up high enough that the healing here paired with [Just Roll With It](item_71918d53-d84e-48f1-9940-8fbe0d9d5a41) will pretty much get you back up to max HP.

Much like last round, [Talon Modification Module](item_c0ca1795-a3ea-4dc9-ae17-f34122574b3a) is the generalist option you can take or if you are on the poorer end on cash.

[Codebreaker](item_caa96c7e-655f-4d03-9bd9-0f41937fec27) as usual is to target the armored tanks.  [Eye of the Spider](item_bbaf01d7-340d-4199-b738-86a98d68fe9b) is one of the best items you can choose to take here as it not only will make your fans hit that much harder but also will make them harder to escape as damage ramps up very fast as they drop to low HP.

The final item you can consider here is [Competitive Analysis](item_168f8109-d2cc-40cc-a6bb-2006a2f62939). This is especially useful in dealing with the abundance of Frejas currently 

Cash Totals
-

[Talon Modification Module](item_c0ca1795-a3ea-4dc9-ae17-f34122574b3a): 32k

[Codebreaker](item_caa96c7e-655f-4d03-9bd9-0f41937fec27): 35k

[Competitive Analysis](item_168f8109-d2cc-40cc-a6bb-2006a2f62939): 37k

[Eye of the Spider](item_bbaf01d7-340d-4199-b738-86a98d68fe9b): 40k

Round Six:
-

On getting to this round, you really should already have enough cash to buy [Eye of the Spider](item_bbaf01d7-340d-4199-b738-86a98d68fe9b) with the other items that you have. You can also sell [Ammo Reserves](item_982d53aa-5ef4-493f-93e7-9e374d0ebf34) for  [Stockpile](item_a113eb56-9999-4f22-9bd7-18f4dbd00cc2) now as even the tiniest amount of attack speed can mean you win or lose now.

If you have more cash, you can opt to sell [Technoleech](item_cb7fd8bf-bdcc-439a-ad35-372f24a027a8) for [Competitive Analysis](item_168f8109-d2cc-40cc-a6bb-2006a2f62939).

Cash Totals
-

[Stockpile](item_a113eb56-9999-4f22-9bd7-18f4dbd00cc2): 48.5k

[Competitive Analysis](item_168f8109-d2cc-40cc-a6bb-2006a2f62939): 52.5k

Round 7:
-

If you already haven't, you are to take [Just Roll With It](item_71918d53-d84e-48f1-9940-8fbe0d9d5a41) now. You must have this power as damage has ramped up so high that the period of invincibility here is very important to your own survival.

If you already got it back in round 5 or have followed the guide and got it in round 3. Then this spot is a free spot. If you want recommendations then [Flash in the Pan](item_b620b463-eda9-4cbe-9781-92fdaf862bdf), [Sunrise](item_750a45f5-bb30-4908-a1ab-b0a3e99d5706), [Easy Rider](item_41b142dd-e362-45dd-884d-a10b1fddddb9) or [Quick Draw](item_fce335e5-8093-4936-98c1-12ee26efd5d3) are good powers to take here. They all have up and downsides, it's just a question of which downside would you prefer to deal with.

As for items, the best and final build you could have is shown on the build list. That being [Technoleech](item_cb7fd8bf-bdcc-439a-ad35-372f24a027a8) for [Competitive Analysis](item_168f8109-d2cc-40cc-a6bb-2006a2f62939) and [Ammo Reserves](item_982d53aa-5ef4-493f-93e7-9e374d0ebf34) for [Stockpile](item_a113eb56-9999-4f22-9bd7-18f4dbd00cc2).

If you need to retain [Ammo Reserves](item_982d53aa-5ef4-493f-93e7-9e374d0ebf34) to buy [Competitive Analysis](item_168f8109-d2cc-40cc-a6bb-2006a2f62939) then so be it, that item is more important anyways

Alternatives for [Competitive Analysis](item_168f8109-d2cc-40cc-a6bb-2006a2f62939) would be [Codebreaker](item_caa96c7e-655f-4d03-9bd9-0f41937fec27) if you want to target the tanks which is a valid target

Cash Totals
-

[Codebreaker](item_caa96c7e-655f-4d03-9bd9-0f41937fec27) over [Competitive Analysis](item_168f8109-d2cc-40cc-a6bb-2006a2f62939) + [Ammo Reserves](item_982d53aa-5ef4-493f-93e7-9e374d0ebf34): 50.5k

[Codebreaker](item_caa96c7e-655f-4d03-9bd9-0f41937fec27) over [Competitive Analysis](item_168f8109-d2cc-40cc-a6bb-2006a2f62939): 53k

[Competitive Analysis](item_168f8109-d2cc-40cc-a6bb-2006a2f62939) + [Ammo Reserves](item_982d53aa-5ef4-493f-93e7-9e374d0ebf34): 52.5k
